## Justin's Learning Profile (Discovered Patterns)

### **Preferences:**
- ‚úÖ **Concrete examples** from actual work (not toy examples)
- ‚úÖ **Top-down** approach (big picture first)
- ‚úÖ **Show and explain** combo (demonstrate then explain why)
- ‚úÖ **High error tolerance** (comfortable iterating)
- ‚úÖ **Moderate density** (concepts + examples, skip deep theory)

### **What Works:**
- ‚úÖ Real code from the project
- ‚úÖ "Here's what we built, here's why it works"
- ‚úÖ Quick iterations with explanations along the way
- ‚úÖ Patterns abstracted from actual solutions
- ‚úÖ Clear cause-and-effect relationships

### **What Doesn't Work:**
- ‚ùå Theoretical examples disconnected from actual work
- ‚ùå Bottom-up building from first principles
- ‚ùå Long explanations before showing something
- ‚ùå Academic/textbook style explanations
- ‚ùå Overly cautious "make sure you understand this first" approaches

### **Teaching Moments That Clicked:**
- ‚úÖ **API Key Management:** Showed actual implementation, then explained pattern
- ‚úÖ **Meeting Automation:** Built working system, then documented approach
- ‚úÖ **Downloads Workflow:** Solved real problem, then abstracted pattern
- ‚úÖ **POC Criteria:** Used real project as example

### **Failed Tutorial Pattern:**
- ‚ùå Tried to teach theoretical concepts first
- ‚ùå Disconnected from actual work
- ‚ùå Too slow, too cautious
- ‚ùå User wanted to "just do it and learn along the way"

**Lesson:** Justin learns by doing, then understanding. Not understanding, then doing.

